data.description: This 2/2 in the much-desired Harder Hall area is very close to the YMCA and Max Long sports complex. This home has been very well maintained and updated. New AC and roof in 2018.  Updated kitchen with recessive lighting.  Wood plank tile throughout the main living area with custom epoxy flooring in both bathrooms for added slip resistance for residents both old and young.  A very spacious master bedroom with dual closets, as well as a large walk-in closet. A screened-in porch with epoxy flooring that is made with custom phosphorescent vinal flake (glows in the dark) for that added wow factor.  The back yard features a new 6-foot fence built in 2022 that's perfect for animals and children.  You also have a detached shed with electric, perfect for a workshop or perhaps a crafting area.  The drain field was also replaced in 2019 that saves a huge expense for many years to come.  Whether you are a first-time buyer or looking for that place to spend your retirement days in without having to waste time doing repairs.
